    steps: ["Set a 25 mm depth gauge on the vessel bottom; lower each shaft until the paddle/basket touches the gauge, then measure the actual distance from the inside bottom to the bottom of the paddle/basket.","Compare to the 25 mm target.","Confirm each vessel is within +/- 2 mm (USP <711>); apply the tighter +/- 1 mm if your site uses enhanced mechanical calibration.","Record each vessel in the data table."],
    attach: "Per-vessel height measurements.",
    summary: {"cols":["Vessel","Measured height (mm)","Target 25 mm","Tolerance (+/- 2 mm)","Pass/Fail"],"rows":6},
    tableLabel: "Data table",
