  "autoclave|PQ|1": {
    "pre": [
      "Mapping / penetration via a Kaye Validator or Ellab ValSuite (wireless RTD loggers, or wired Type-T TCs through a leak-tight feed-through), ice-point + steam-point verified pre- and post-study (gate ± 0.5 C); F0 computed at Z = 10 C, Tref 121.1 C.",
      "Defined worst-case load installed (max/densest/hardest-to-penetrate) per the load-pattern map.",
      "10-15 penetration TCs available for the slowest-to-heat points; one independent calibrated reference TC; BIs (>= 10^6 G. stearothermophilus ATCC 12980/7953) for cold-spot co-location.",
      "Pre-study TC calibration recorded (e.g. 3-point, ± 0.5 C); F0 integration configured (base 121.1 C, z=10); data logged >= 1/sec, all channels synchronized."
    ],
    "steps": [
      "Install the worst-case load per the load-pattern map (densest / hardest-to-penetrate).",
      "Place 10-15 penetration TCs at the slowest-to-heat points: inside representative product units (worst-case fill/closure), the densest pack centre, near the drain, chamber corners, and near the door; tip in contact with the item or in the coldest fluid. Co-locate a BI with the cold-spot TC and add one independent reference TC. Record each S/N vs position.",
      "Run the sterilization cycle; record the equilibration time (slowest point into the band) and the hold.",
      "Integrate F0 at each TC (base 121.1 C, z=10) and identify the load cold spot (lowest F0).",
      "Recover and incubate the co-located BIs with positive and negative controls.",
      "Repeat for 3 consecutive cycles and confirm the cold-spot location is consistent run-to-run.",
      "Record per-position min temp, F0, and BI result in the table."
    ],
    "attach": "Raw and analyzed penetration TC data with F0 integration (all positions), the load-pattern map, and pre/post calibration records.",
    "summary": {
      "cols": [
        "Position",
        "TC S/N",
        "Min temp in hold (°C)",
        "F0 delivered (min)",
        "BI growth?",
        "Pass/Fail"
      ],
      "rows": 6,
      "rowLabels": [
        "Worst-case cold spot (OQ)",
        "Load position A",
        "Load position B",
        "Load position C",
        "Centre of load",
        "Co-located with BI"
      ]
    },
    "tableLabel": "Results summary",
    "chart": {
      "shape": "saturation",
      "x": "Time (min)",
      "y": "F0 delivered (min)",
      "limit": {
        "y": 0.62,
        "label": ">= 12 min (overkill)"
      },
      "caption": "F0 accumulates through the temperature plateau; the load cold spot must reach the required lethality (>= 12 min overkill benchmark, or a justified bioburden-based target)."
    },
    "accept": [
      "F0 at the worst-case cold spot meets the cycle requirement - a moist-heat overkill cycle commonly targets F0 >= 15 min (reference 121.1 C, z = 10 C); a bioburden-based cycle targets its validated value.",
      "The paired BI at the cold spot shows no growth.",
      "F0 is the integrated lethality the slowest point received - overkill cycles carry a large margin."
    ],
    "note": "F0 at the COLD SPOT is the whole game for a moist-heat cycle - it's the integrated lethality the slowest point received. Overkill cycles target a large margin; bioburden/biovalidation cycles justify a lower F0 with BIs. PDA TR 48 (Moist Heat Sterilizer Systems, 2010) is the PDA companion for the design, commissioning, and qualification of these systems."
  },
